## What Is Web Application Development? (explainer block)

A website shows information. A **web application** does something — it lets users log in, interact with data, complete tasks, and get results back in real time.

Think of the difference between a restaurant's homepage (a website — informational, mostly static) and an online table-booking system with live availability, confirmations, and an admin dashboard to manage reservations (a web application — interactive, dynamic, built on custom logic).

Web application development means building that second kind of system — software that runs in the browser but behaves like a full product: with user accounts, a database behind it, business rules baked into the logic, and an interface designed around how people actually use it.

This is different from picking a WordPress theme or a no-code builder. It's software engineering — architecture, database design, and custom logic — built specifically for your use case rather than adapted from a generic template.

