## What's Included in This Service

### 1. Requirement Analysis & System Design
Before any code is written, the actual problem gets mapped out properly.

- Understanding your workflow, users, and what the application needs to do
- Defining the data model — what information the system needs to store and how it connects
- Choosing the right architecture for your scale (a 50-user internal tool doesn't need the same setup as a 50,000-user product)

### 2. Frontend Development
The interface your users interact with — built for clarity and speed, not just visual polish.

- Built with **React** and **Next.js** for fast, responsive, interactive interfaces
- Dashboards, forms, tables, and workflows designed around real usage patterns
- Fully responsive — works properly on mobile, tablet, and desktop
- **TypeScript** for fewer bugs and easier long-term maintenance

### 3. Backend & Business Logic
The engine that actually runs your application's rules and processes.

- Built with **FastAPI** or **Node.js**, depending on project needs
- Custom business logic — approval workflows, calculations, automated processes specific to your operations
- Secure API architecture connecting frontend to database
- Third-party integrations (payment gateways, email, external services, existing internal tools)

### 4. User Authentication & Access Control
Making sure the right people see the right things.

- Secure login and account management
- Role-based access control — admins, managers, and regular users each see only what they should
- Multi-user support with proper data isolation where needed

### 5. Database Architecture
The foundation everything else depends on.

- **PostgreSQL** (via Supabase) — reliable, scalable, with real-time capabilities built in
- Schema designed to handle your actual data relationships correctly from day one
- Avoids the common mistake of a database structure that works at launch but breaks at scale

### 6. Deployment & Ongoing Reliability
Getting it live, and keeping it running.

- Production deployment with proper environment setup
- Performance monitoring and error tracking
- A defined post-launch support window to catch issues early

